'''Jekyll'''是一个简单的[[网页模板引擎系统|静态网站生成器]]，用于生成个人，项目或组织的网站。 它由[[GitHub|GitHub]]联合创始人[[汤姆·普雷斯顿·沃纳|汤姆·普雷斯顿·沃纳]]用[[Ruby|Ruby]]编写，并根据[[MIT许可证|MIT许可证]]发布。

== 历史 ==
Jekyll由Tom Preston-Werner于2008年首次发布。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Blogging Like a Hacker|url=http://tom.preston-werner.com/2008/11/17/blogging-like-a-hacker.html|accessdate=2015-10-10|author=Preston-Werner|date=2008-11-17|first=Tom|work=Preston-Werner.com|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116002339/https://tom.preston-werner.com/2008/11/17/blogging-like-a-hacker.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> Jekyll后来被帕克·摩尔（Parker Moore）接管，並由他领导发布Jekyll 1的工作，之后的维护者一直还是他。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Interview with Parker Moore from Jekyll|url=https://www.netlify.com/blog/2016/03/11/interview-with-parker-moore-from-jekyll/|accessdate=2020-08-19|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108114217/https://www.netlify.com/blog/2016/03/11/interview-with-parker-moore-from-jekyll/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

Jekyll开始向[[静态网页|静态网站]]的Web开发趋势。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Static Website Generators Reviewed: Jekyll, Middleman, Roots, Hugo|url=https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/11/static-website-generators-jekyll-middleman-roots-hugo-review/|accessdate=2016-02-10|author=Christensen|date=2015-11-16|first=Mathias Biilmann|work=Smashing Magazine|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205224043/https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/11/static-website-generators-jekyll-middleman-roots-hugo-review/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 截至2017年，Jekyll成为了最受欢迎的静态站点生成器，这在很大程度上是因为它被[[GitHub|GitHub]]所采用。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Top Ten Static Site Generators of 2017 {{!}} Netlify|url=https://www.netlify.com/blog/2017/05/25/top-ten-static-site-generators-of-2017/|accessdate=2018-02-11|work=Netlify|archive-date=2020-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104174303/https://www.netlify.com/blog/2017/05/25/top-ten-static-site-generators-of-2017/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 特点 ==
Jekyll不使用[[数据库|数据库]] ，用户通过编写[[Markdown|Markdown]]、[[纺织品（标记语言）|Textile]]或Liquid文件， 生成一个完整的静态网站，并且可以由[[Apache_HTTP_Server|Apache HTTP Server]] ， [[Nginx|Nginx]]或其他[[Web服务器|Web服务器]]提供服务。 <ref name="readme">{{Cite web|title=README.markdown for Jekyll software|url=https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/blob/master/README.markdown|accessdate=February 19, 2014|publisher=Jekyll's authors|archive-date=2015-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810133318/https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/blob/master/README.markdown|dead-url=no}}</ref> Jekyll是[[GitHub|GitHub Pages]]的引擎。 <ref name="github_pages">{{Cite web|title=GitHub Pages|url=https://jekyllrb.com/docs/github-pages/|accessdate=February 19, 2014|publisher=Jekyll's authors|archive-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702081936/https://jekyllrb.com/docs/github-pages/|dead-url=no}}</ref>  

Jekyll非常灵活，可以与[[Bootstrap|Bootstrap]] ， <ref>{{Cite news|author=Patton|first=Tony|title=Build full-featured sites with Jekyll, Bootstrap, and GitHub|work=TechRepublic|accessdate=2015-10-11|date=2014-07-16|url=https://www.techrepublic.com/article/build-full-featured-sites-with-jekyll-bootstrap-and-github/|archive-date=2017-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171215110726/https://www.techrepublic.com/article/build-full-featured-sites-with-jekyll-bootstrap-and-github/|dead-url=no}}</ref>Semantic UI等[[Web应用框架|前端框架]]结合使用。 

Jekyll网站可以连接到基于云的[[内容管理系统|CMS]]软件，例如[[CloudCannon|CloudCannon]]，Forestry， [[Netlify|Netlify]]或Siteleaf，使编辑者无需知道如何编程即可修改网站内容。 

== Jekyll的哲学 ==
来自Jekyll的[[Readme|自述文件]] <ref>{{Cite web|title=README|url=https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/blob/master/README.markdown|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=October 18, 2018|archive-date=2015-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150810133318/https://github.com/jekyll/jekyll/blob/master/README.markdown|dead-url=no}}</ref> ： <blockquote> Jekyll does what you tell it to do — no more, no less. It doesn't try to outsmart users by making bold assumptions, nor does it burden them with needless complexity and configuration. Put simply, Jekyll gets out of your way and allows you to concentrate on what truly matters: your content. </blockquote>

